│ THOUGHT: So samesign is a flag on icmp instruction. The issue is that when we truncate operands, we might change the sign relationship. The transformation should preserve the samesign flag only if           │
│ truncation preserves sign information. In our case, truncating %x from i32 to i8 preserves the value (0) and sign (non-negative). However, %call2 is -128 as i8 but was 128 as i32 after zext. The zext        │
│ changes the sign: i8 -128 (negative) becomes i32 128 (positive). So the original comparison `icmp samesign ugt i32 %x, %ext` compares non-negative %x (0) with positive %ext (128). Both have same sign        │
│ (non-negative/positive). After transformation, we compare i8 0 (non-negative) with i8 -128 (negative). Signs differ, so samesign ugt is poison.                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The problem is that the transformation is eliminating the zext and truncating %x, but it's not considering that zext changes the sign of %call2. Actually, looking at the code: `%ext = zext i8 %call2 to      │
│ i32`. The zext converts i8 to i32, preserving value but zero-extending. If %call2 is i8 128 (which is -128 signed), zext produces i32 128 (positive). So the sign changes from negative to positive. The       │
│ samesign flag in the original icmp is valid because both operands are non-negative (%x is in [0,32), %ext is positive 128). After transformation, we have `icmp samesign ugt i8 %0, %call2` where %0 is 0      │
│ (non-negative) and %call2 is -128 (negative). Signs differ, so samesign is invalid.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The transformation should either:                                                                                                                                                                              │
│ 1. Drop the samesign flag when narrowing if sign information might change                                                                                                                                      │
│ 2. Not apply the narrowing transformation when samesign flag is set                                                                                                                                            │
